Create a Template from an Einstein Bot

Use a bot as the basis for a bot template. You can package bot templates and share them between orgs or on AppExchange.

Einstein Bots is available in Salesforce Classic and Lightning Experience. Setup for Einstein Bots is available in Lightning Experience.
Available in: Enterprise, Performance, Unlimited, and Developer Editions

To build and manage Einstein Bots:
Customize Application
OR
Modify Metadata
OR
Manage Bots

A template is supported for either standard or enhanced bot types. When you create a template from an existing bot, the template can be used to create a bot of the same type only.

Before a bot can become a template, you must remove unsupported elements from the bot version. These elements include:
Transfer actions
Einstein Intent Sets
Enhanced messaging components

From the Einstein Bots main page, go to the bot you want to use to create a template.
Click to expand the bot versions, and then select the dropdown next to the version of the bot you want to use to create a template.
Click Create Template from Bot.

Give your template a name, and set a primary language and any secondary languages. Optionally, you can add a permission set to your template so any bots created from your template have access to required resources, such as objects and flows. Save your changes.

The Bot Builder opens with your new template.
title: Create a Template from an Einstein Bot in Service Cloud
